This paper focuses on the use of machine learning algorithms for the detection of ransomware, specifically crypto-ransomware. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper uses Support Vector Machine (SVM) and attribute selection methods, which are commonly used in the fields of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the use of WEKA, a popular tool for data mining and machine learning, which falls under the category of Software Engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of data and the use of algorithms, which are relevant to the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
